    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-19T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-19T01:00:00-05:00" n="373"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7403: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-19T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 19, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>89. This Embassy’s 85, November 18, 2 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Reuter has distributed another news despatch “for information only” dated
                        Shanghai November 18 stating that Rengo had received a despatch from Peiping
                        to the effect that the five Northern provinces are to declare autonomy
                        November 20 and that the following had been named as members of the
                        “Preparatory Committee” for the establishment of the new North China
                        Administration: Sung Cheyuan; Han Fu-chu; Shang Chen; Chin Teh-chun; Hsiao
                        Chen-ying, Chahar Chairman; Wan Fu-lin; Chang Keh; and Yin Ju-keng,
                        Administrative Commissioner for the Lwantung area.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Suma stated this morning that he will be greatly surprised if an
                        autonomous movement is announced tomorrow. He predicted that disorders in
                        North China will increase.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>By mail to Shanghai for the Ambassador and to Tokyo.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
